Incredible ramen, incredible service, incredible music! I got the fungi ramen and a dealer's choice flight of sake. The server was super helpful and attentive. I was also really impressed with the ramen-- sometimes vegetarian options can be really bland, but this was rich and great proportions of everything in it. Unfortunately this place falls under my "overhyped" category. Nothing stood out as good and one dish was just horrible. Came here on a Saturday afternoon around 1 PM. There were a handful of parties so we didn't have to wait to get seated. A waitress came by and blurted out the special of the day, but she spoke so fast and in such a low voice that I didn't even bother paying attention. We ordered pork belly bao appetizers, scallop cone-sushi, and belly bowl ramen. The pork belly bao dish consisted of three baos. The amount of pork in each bao was on the small side and there wasn't much flavor. The ramen was just okay. The most disappointing dish had to be the scallop cone-sushi. First of all, the name is misleading as it's not a cone or hand roll which is what I was thinking. The dish is actually risotto with scallops stuffed in a tofu pouch. There are three of these pouches to be precise. Each one filled with hard scallops and undercooked risotto. It was so awful that I simply ate the tofu pouch and left the risotto and scallops on the plate. The atmosphere is nice and chill with a cool bar and some tables along the back wall and windows. Not a bad place to sit and take a break from the heat outside...just wished the food was better.

These are some fine buns!! It's been almost half a decade since I've been here and the food is just as amazing as I remembered! We sat at the bar and ordered a lucky bowl and trio of appetizers. I'm not sure if he was the owner/co-owner or just a really good bartender, but he made all these great recommendations and was engaging in conversation with all the guests. Since I'm allergic to shrimp, he let me choose another appetizer in place of the lobster shumai. The dumplings are still just as delicious as ever!!! And the baos have crispy on the outside, juicy on the inside pork belly. The ambiance is perfect for date night. I need to come here more often ... but I will definitely be back!

Great little spot with a great vibe and cool music.  It's hilarious but the food menu was on one page, where the drinks, cocktails and libations were spread out on three pages!  My sister and I had the pork bao which was super delicious!  Have you ever been to a fancy shmanzy Chinese wedding that served those yummy white bun with the think crispy duck skin?  If you love that , you will love this bao!  We also got the beet salad.  It comes with four pieces of beet layered with goat cheese.  Very nicely done.  It says spicy greens but it just means the greens have a sharp flavor.  We both had ramen, I had the fungi ramen and sister had their signature.  Both were delicious but they under salt it so you can add flavor as you wish.  Overall great experience would love to go again!

We went here for lunch on a Monday. It opens at 11:00AM and fills up pretty quick. We ordered the daily bento and the pork belly bowl. I'm not a fan of Ramen but it was delicious. The pork has a really great smoked flavour. The broth has a lot of seaweed and is really fast. The Bento box was swordfish, salad and a pork Bao. The portions were large. Service was friendly and efficient. Good value and great food. We will return, even if we have to rent a car since we live in Canada.
